INSERT INTO notice VALUES (1,'01/22/01','Contact Protocol','For the beta period, we will have only one contact email available. This is because at this time, we have an extremely limited Customer Support team. (basically me, but I am also wearing some other hats at this point) We will be improving this later, but at this stage, it is more important that we have more of a tech-oriented team to better fix problems. \r\nSo, let me apologize in advance if sometimes you messages are not responded to swiftly, or not at all. I will try to address all sensible messages I receive. I also ask that you limit your content to the following types of messages: Cheating reports (cringe), Questions on game play (only after you have read the beginners guide please), strategies that you feel are very effective (these may not be responded to, but will help us when we begin to improve the beginners guide), and finally, anyone who wants to send money may email me for information. : ) \r\n\r\nFor those of you with suggestions, I ask that you not email them. There will be a forum available for suggestions. We will read this and occasionally ask your opinions. Thank you for your cooperation and I hope you enjoy the game.\r\n\r\n-birdman\r\n');
INSERT INTO notice VALUES (2,'01/22/01','Bug Reporting','We realize that there are bugs still remaining in our game. We ask that you help us during this beta testing period so that we may improve Archspace for everyone. If you encounter what you believe is a bug, please post a message on the bug bulletin board in the Forum section. We ask that you include the following information and use this general format. \r\n\r\nPortal Login: \r\nCharacter Name and Number: \r\nTime of Bug: \r\nPage you were on: \r\nThe bug itself: What was the problem you noticed. What message did you \r\n                     receive? \r\nWhat recent actions had you taken with your character: \r\n\r\nIf you use this format, it will be easier for us to interpret, and the more information you can provide, the more likely it is that we will be able to locate the problem. Also, be aware that some bugs may seem simple, but they may take time to fix, because there may either be more severe bugs that must be fixed first, or this bug is a symptom of a larger bug, or more complicated than it seems. \r\n\r\n-birdman\r\n');
INSERT INTO notice VALUES (3,'01/23/01','Archspace Public Beta','We invite you to join us in this new world we are creating. As this is a testing period, there will be some changes made while the game is running. There will also be times when the game will be down for updating. We ask that you be patient with us. We realize there are still bugs remaining in the game. That is why we are doing this beta test. If you encounter a bug, please use the form provided to report it. There is an message following this which gives more details for bug reporting. Also, we will be occasionally be implementing new features. Some of these that we are planning are: Black Market, Events, Active Empire interaction, Spies, many minor additions. For now, we ask that you not send suggestions for adding things to the game. To contact us for other reasons, please read the message titled contact protocol.\r\n\r\nWell, once again, welcome. Enjoy Archspace. \r\n\r\n-birdman\r\n');
INSERT INTO notice VALUES (4,'01/23/01','Bugs that you should know about right away.','There are two very common problems with the game right now. \r\n\r\nThe first in the Apache .... Error. This is quite common and is the cause for the second bug. We are uncertain of one of the causes. When there are short down time, we have not pinpointed the reason, but we have clues and are on the trail. When there is a long down time, that means we have found a bug and have had to recompile the game. This second case is good for everyone, because it means the game is at least a little more stable. \r\n\r\nThe Second bug has been dubbed the Roll-back bug. This occurs often when the first bug occurs. What happens is that recent orders or events are sometimes undone. This can be quite frustrating, we know. \r\n\r\nTo sum up, it is asked that if you encounter these bugs, please have patience. It is just a matter of time until we find the cause. We are aware of them. \r\n\r\n\r\n-birdman \r\n\r\nps Also, I appreciate the thanks for my efforts, but at this point, my main job is just talking with you. Our coders and designers are doing the hard part. You should thank them.\r\n');
INSERT INTO notice VALUES (5,'01/26/01','Apache Bug fixed. Also, a Reset','Well, after days of around the clock searching, the cause of the bug was found. It has been fixed, and the game should be much more stable now. Unfortunately for some, (but asked for by others) we are forced to reset the server. This is because the old database had too much pre-fix info stored. This made it quite unstable. With the fix, and the reset, the game should be much more stable. Also, many other \"bugs\" should now disappear, as they were only side effects of the Apache bug. A major one of these is the rollback bug. This should no longer occur.\r\n\r\nAs for what the reset entails. Your characters have all been wiped. You will have to remake your portal ID. We apologize for this, and we will only reset in major cases such as this. However, in this case, we feel it was more than justified, as the game was almost unplayable with this bug in effect.\r\n\r\nAnyways, good luck in the new game, and may the best sentient being win!!!!\r\n\r\n-birdman\r\n');
INSERT INTO notice VALUES (6,'01/30/01','New Text Version is Step by Step available.','As some people were having problems with the image intesive step by step, we have added a Text Version. The Graphic version is still available, there is a link to switch between them near the top of the main step by step page.\r\n\r\n-birdman\r\n');
INSERT INTO notice VALUES (7,'02/01/01','Server Down for Maintenance','There will be server shutdown for maintenace from Feb. 1. 13:00 to 17:00 PST.\r\n');
INSERT INTO notice VALUES (8,'02/09/01','Diplomatic Status Reset','We have found the cause of all the changes in Diplomatic status. We have fixed this cause. However, we cannot reset to what you wanted to be set as, so we will have to reset all diplomatic states to neutral.\r\n\r\n-birdman\r\n');

